The evidence with the title 'Energy secretary puzzled by stupid question from rep. Joe Barton ... ' says Apr 22, 2009  ... Rep. Joe Barton ( R - Texas) posted this exchange with energy secretary  ... Wind is the way you shift heat from areas where it 's hotter to areas where it's cooler.  ... Which slows the winds down , which causes the temperature to go up?  ... You stop something , you can't transfer that heat, and the heat goes up. 
